images.description: Fredrik Carl Mülert Størmer (1874-1957) was a Norwegian mathematician, astrophysicist and photographer. As a student in the 1890s he obtained a C.P. Stirn spy camera, also known as a Grays Vest Concealed. The camera was concealed under his jacket with the lens hidden in a button hole. Størmer would walk the streets of Christiania (now Oslo) and greet people with his hat to get their attention and a reaction, then secretly take a photo. The results offer an interesting look at people in their natural state, as opposed to the strict posing trends that dominated in photography at the time.
Playwright Henrik Ibsen at the Egertorget.
